author: National Geographic
description:
The monarch’s 3,000-mile migration is one of the most epic and dangerous journeys on Earth. Each fall, butterflies born in Canada and the U.S. navigate south to the same Mexican fir groves that sheltered their grandparents and great-grandparents. But habitat loss and extreme weather are pushing this iconic traveler toward the edge—raising urgent questions about whether the migration can survive.

author: National Geographic
description:
From Cleopatra to King Tut, join National Geographic in this Lost Treasures of Egypt mega episode to uncover the secrets of the lost tombs of one of the most mysterious ancient civilizations. Featuring Full Episodes:

Secrets of the Mummy Tombs 
Archaeologists attempt to decode ancient Egyptian beliefs in the afterlife. Hidden tombs and a sealed sarcophagus give up their secrets.

Secrets of the Mega Tombs 
Archaeologists explore a series of spectacular mega tombs to reconstruct the story of a mysterious chapter of ancient Egyptian history.

Mystery of Tut's Tomb 
Archaeologists investigate the mystery of Tutankhamun’s small and poorly decorated tomb. Why was the Boy King banished to a tomb hardly fit for a Pharaoh?

Pyramid Tomb Raiders 
Archaeologists investigate how robbers looted the pyramids and tombs of ancient Egypt, and what clues they left behind.

author: National Geographic
description:
The Battle of Kadesh stands as the largest chariot battle ever recorded in history, with over 5,000 chariots thundering across the battlefield in a clash so monumental it was literally carved into stone. On one side, the Egyptian army led by Ramses II; on the other, the Hittite Empire—but who won? 

Learn more about the Hittites: https://on.natgeo.com/3KQr44T

Host: Amy Briggs
